---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Series";
const description = "Collections of connected essays, research arcs, and thematic writing series.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <section class="section">
    <h1>Series</h1>
    <p>
      Multi-part work designed to unfold across systems, not just publish individual ideas.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- SERIES I -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">

    <p class="series-label">Series I</p>
    <h3>Human-Governed Intelligence Systems</h3>
    <p class="series-description">
      A five-part framework for governing AI-mediated intelligence systems under conditions of ambiguity, pressure, and risk.
    </p>

    <div class="series-list">

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.1</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/toward-a-human-centered-intelligence-infrastructure/">Toward a Human-Governed Intelligence Infrastructure</a></h3>
        <p>Establishes the case for treating AI-enabled intelligence systems as governed infrastructure, not passive tools.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.2</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/operational-empathy-as-intelligence-capability/">Operational Empathy as Intelligence Capability</a></h3>
        <p>Reframes human context as a core capability for interpretation under ambiguity and incomplete signal.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.3</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/the-civic-signal/">The Civic Signal</a></h3>
        <p>Positions trust, sentiment, and engagement as measurable inputs that shape intelligence outcomes.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.4</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/signal-integrity/">Signal Integrity</a></h3>
        <p>Defines governance mechanisms to detect drift, resist distortion, and maintain alignment with reality.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.5</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/designed-lives/">Designed Lives</a></h3>
        <p>Translates system design into human consequence, showing how intelligence systems shape lived experience.</p>
      </article>

    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- TRANSITION -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">
    <p class="series-transition">
      This series defines the system. The next puts it under load.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- SERIES II -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">

    <p class="series-label">Series II</p>
    <h3>From Framework to Fielding</h3>
    <p class="series-description">
      A five-part series on implementation, measurement, workflow design, architecture, and institutional adoption.
    </p>

    <div class="series-list">

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">II.1</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/from-design-to-decision/">From Design to Decision</a></h3>
        <p>Defines how human-governed intelligence systems are implemented under real-world conditions, translating governance into decision-level control.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">II.2</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/measuring-signal-integrity/">Measuring Signal Integrity</a></h3>
        <p>Defines how signal integrity is measured in AI-mediated systems, turning accuracy, error, and trust into enforceable controls.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">II.3</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/designing-analyst-workflows/">Designing Analyst Workflows</a></h3>
        <p>Defines how analyst workflows must be structured to preserve accuracy, context, and control in AI-mediated intelligence systems.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">II.4</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/system-architecture-for-governed-intelligence/">System Architecture for Governed Intelligence</a></h3>
        <p>Defines how system architecture enforces governance, embedding control, auditability, and signal integrity into intelligence systems.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">II.5</p>
        <h3><a href="/writing/institutional-adoption-and-change/">Institutional Adoption and Change</a></h3>
        <p>Defines how governed intelligence systems are adopted in practice, aligning incentives, leadership, and behavior to sustain accuracy and control.</p>
      </article>

    </div>

  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .series-label {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .series-description {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .series-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .series-list article {
    display: grid;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .item-number {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .series-list h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.28rem;
    line-height: 1.28;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .series-list h3 a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .series-list h3 a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .series-list article > p:last-child {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .series-transition {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 40rem;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }
</style>